label.value: Classical swine fever virus E2 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A E2 mutant in Classical swine fever virus is attenuated and provides protection in pigs after oronasal vaccination (not intradermal vaccination) against lethal challenge dose of CSFV strain Eystrup

label.value: Equid herpesvirus gE mutant vaccine

definition.value: A glycoprotein E mutant is attenuated in mice and hamsters and induced significant protection from challenge with wild type Equid herpesvirus in mice

label.value: Equid herpesvirus gI mutant vaccine

definition.value: A glycoprotein I mutant is attenuated in mice and hamsters and induced significant protection from challenge with wild type Equid herpesvirus in mice

label.value: Equid herpesvirus TK mutant vaccine

definition.value: A thymidine kinase-deficient mutant (PR1) is attenuated in mice and induced significant protection from challenge with wild type EHV-1 5 weeks after vaccination. In foals, PR1 also showed attenuation; however, the mutant induced only partial protection from challenge with EHV-1

label.value: Feline herpesvirus 1 UL23 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A thymidine kinase-deficient mutant (C7301dlTK) is attenuated in cats and induced significant protection from wild type FHV-1 4 weeks after vaccination

label.value: Feline immunodeficiency virus ORF-A mutant vaccine

definition.value: Feline immunodeficiency virus (FIV) made defective in the accessory gene ORF-A were previously shown to be greatly attenuated in its ability to replicate in lymphocytes but to grow normally or near normally in other cell types. 3/9 vaccinees (cats) showed no evidence of the challenge virus over a 15-month observation period. In the other vaccinees, the challenge virus was predominant for various periods of time, but pre-existing viral loads and CD4 lymphocyte counts were either unaffected or altered only marginally and transiently

label.value: Feline immunodeficiency virus vif mutant vaccine

definition.value: A vif mutant in feline immunodeficiency virus was attenuated and a vif-deleted FIV provirus DNA protected cats against challenge with the homologous FIV-PPR biological isolate.

label.value: Feline infectiour peritonitis virus 3abc mutant vaccine

definition.value: A 3abc deletion mutant in Feline infectious peritonitis virus (FIPV) was attenuated and provided protection against virulent FIPV strain 79-1146 challenge in kittens

label.value: Feline infectious peritonitis virus 7ab mutant vaccine

definition.value: A 7ab deletion mutant in Feline infectious peritonitis virus is attenuated and provides protection against virulent FIPV strain 79-1146 challenge in kittens

label.value: Gallid herpesvirus 1 UL0 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UL0 mutant in infectious laryngotracheitis virus (ILTV) was attenuated. Chickens immunized with UL0-negative ILTV were protected from clinical disease after subsequent infection with virulent ILTV

label.value: Gallid herpesvirus 1 UL23 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A thymidine-kinase mutant is attenuated in chickens and induced protection from challenge with wild type GHV-1

label.value: Gallid herpesvirus 1 UL47 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UL47 mutant in avian infectious laryngotracheitis virus is attenuated and provides protection in chicken against subsequent challenge infection with virulent ILTV

label.value: Hepatitis B virus X protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: Researchers generated a series of woodchuck hepatitis virus (WHV) X mutants. Woodchucks inoculated with X mutants, including those with no serologic evidence of infection, were protected from later challenge with infectious Woodchuck Hepatitis Virus, suggesting previous infection with resulting protective immunity

label.value: Herpes simplex virus 1 gD mutant vaccine

definition.value: KOS-gDA3C is attenuated with mutations in gD gene in causing skin lesions at the inoculation and zosteriform sites, yet it is as effective as rKOS-gDA3C in protecting mice against HSV-1 challenge

label.value: Herpes simplex virus 1 gH mutant vaccine

definition.value: A gH mutant is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type HSV-1

label.value: Herpes simplex virus 2 ICP0 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A live-attenuated HSV-2 ICP0 virus provides significant protection against wild-type HSV-2 (MS strain) challenge in mice

label.value: Herpes simplex virus 1 TK mutant vaccine

definition.value: A thymidine kinase-deficient (TK) mutant was found to be attenuated in mice. This mutant induced complete protection from challenge with wild type HSV

label.value: Herpes simplex virus 1 UL29 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UL29 mutant is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type HSV-1

label.value: human metapneumovirus G protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: A G mutant is attenuated in African green monkeys and induces protection from challenge with wild type HMPV

label.value: human metapneumovirus M2-2 mutant vaccine

definition.value: An M2-2 mutant is attenuated in African green monkeys and induced protection from challenge with wild type HMPV

label.value: Human Respiratory Syncytial Virus M2-2 mutant vaccine

definition.value: An M2-2 mutant of human respiratory syncytial virus A2 is attenuated in African green monkeys. When challenged with wild type RSV, two doses provided complete protection against challenge in the lower respiratory tract and a significant reduction of the challenge virus in the upper respiratory tract

label.value: Infectious Hematopoietic Necrosis Virus NV mutant vaccine

definition.value: A mutation in the non-virion protein of IHNV causes attenuated growth in rainbow trout and is able to provide significant protection from subsequent challenge with wild type IHNV

label.value: influenza virus CTA1-3M2e-DD protein vaccine

definition.value: Mutant influenza virus that lacks the transmembrane and cytoplasmic tail domains of M2 (M2 knockout [M2KO]) from Influenza A virus (A/Puerto Rico/8/34(H1N1)) is attenuated in both cell culture and mice. Mice intranasally vaccinated with M2KO virus developed protective immune responses and survived a lethal challenge with the wild-type virus, suggesting that the M2KO virus has potential as a live attenuated vaccine

label.value: influenza virus NS1 mutant vaccine

definition.value: Intranasal inoculation of mice, pigs, horses, and macaques with NS1-modified influenza virus strains induced robust humoral and cellular immune responses, and generated immune protection against challenge with wild-type virus

label.value: Porcine respiratory and reproductive syndrome virus GP5 protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: A mutation in the GP5 protein attenuates HP-PRRSV in piglets. This mutant (HuN4-F112) induces protection against challenge with wild type HP-PRRSV

label.value: Pseudorabies virus glycoprotein E/G/UL23 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UL23 mutant, in combination with mutations in glycoproteins G and E, is attenuated in raccoons, with a 75% survival rate. This mutant also provides some protection from wild type PRV
A glycoprotein E mutant, in combination with UL23 and glycoprotein G mutations, is attenuated in raccoons, with a 75% survival rate. This mutant also provides some protection from wild type PRV
A glycoprotein G mutant, in combination with UL23 and glycoprotein E mutations, is attenuated in raccoons, with a 75% survival rate. This mutant also provides some protection from wild type PRV

label.value: Psuedorabies virus glycoprotein M mutant vaccine

definition.value: A glycoprotein M, gM, deletion in pseudorabies virus was attenuated and induced protection in piglets against intranasal challenge with 108 p.f.u. of the highly virulent PrV strain NIA-3

label.value: Pseudorabies virus gp50/gp63 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A gp50+gp63 deletion mutant in Pseudorabies virus was attenuated and provided protection from clinical signs of Aujeszky's disease after a challenge inoculation with the virulent wild-type PRV strain NIA-3

label.value: Pseudorabies virus UL50 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UL50 mutant is attenuated in pseudorabies virus and induces significant protection in pigs from challenge with the highly virulent NIA-3 strain of PrV

label.value: Pseudorabies virus US3 mutant vaccine

definition.value: Researchers intranasally inoculated pigs, the natural host of this virus, with mutant PRV strains in which the genes encoding the protein kinase (US3) proteins were inactivated. After challenge infection with the virulent PRV strain NIA-3, no virus was excreted by wt PRV- and PK- mutant-immunized animals, indicating complete protective immunity

label.value: Rabies virus glycoprotein G mutant vaccine

definition.value: A glycoprotein G mutant in rabies virus is attenuated. After a one-dose intramuscular vaccination, the ERAg3m virus protected 100% of mice and hamsters from lethal challenge. In co-infections, using a lethal dose of street rabies virus mixed with ERAg3m, 100% of hamsters and 90% of mice survived and were protected against subsequent infection

label.value: Rabies virus P protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: A P gene mutant is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type Rabies virus

label.value: SARS-CoV E gene mutant vaccine

definition.value: An E mutant is attenuated in hamsters and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type SARS

label.value: Simian Immunodeficiency Virus nef mutant vaccine

definition.value: A SIV nef mutant is attenuated in rhesus monkeys and induces protection from challenge with wild type SIV

label.value: ick-borne Encephalitis Virus C protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: A virus with a mutation in protein C is attenuated in mice and induced protection from challenge with wild type TBE virus

label.value: VEE Virus PE2/E1 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A VEE mutant with a PE2 cleavage signal mutation and a suppressor mutation in E1 is highly attenuated in mice and provides complete protection against challenge with wild type VEE

label.value: West Nile virus C protein mutant vaccine

definition.value: A virus with a C protein mutation is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type West Nile virus

label.value: Western equine encephalomyelitis virus PE2/E1 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A PE2 mutant combined with a deletion in E1 (WE2130) induced low-level viremia in chickens and protected against challenge with wild type WEE after 2 weeks. This study also found that it is unlikely that mosquito transmission of this strain would occur

label.value: Western equine encephalomyelitis virus PE2/E2 mutant virus

definition.value: A PE2 mutant combined with a deletion in E2 (WE2102) induced low-level viremia in chickens and protected against challenge with wild type WEE after 2 weeks. This study also found that it is unlikely that mosquito transmission of this strain would occur

label.value: Western equine encephalomyelitis virus PE2/E1 or E2 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A PE2 mutant combined with either a deletion in E2 (WE2102) or E1 (WE2130) induced low-level viremia in chickens and protected against challenge with wild type WEE after 2 weeks. This study also found that it is unlikely that mosquito transmission of these two strains would occur

label.value: Leishmania donovani cen1 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A cen1 mutant is attenuated in mice and hamsters and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type L. donovani

label.value: Leishmania infantum HSP70 II mutant vaccine

definition.value: A Leishmania infantum deletion mutant of HSP70-II gene is attenuated and provides protection against Leishmania infection in the L. major-BALB/c infection model. Also, DeltaHSP70-II is a safe live vaccine as immunodeficient SCID mice, and hamsters, infected with mutant parasites did not develp any sign of pathology

label.value: Plasmodium FabB/FabF mutant vaccine

definition.value: A genetically attenuated parasite (GAP) with a mutation in the FabB/FabF gene is attenuated in mice by arresting in the late liver stage. It also conferred complete protection in mice from challenge with wild type Plasmodium

label.value: P. berghei p36p mutant vaccine

definition.value: Genetically attenuated P36p-deficient Plasmodium berghei sporozoites provide protection against sporozoites challenge in mice

label.value: P. yoelii p36/p52 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A genetically attenuated parasite (GAP) with deletions in p52 and p36 are attenuated in mice. Mice immunized with the mutant were completely protected against challenge with wild type Plasmodium sporozoites

label.value: P. yoelii UIS3 mutant vaccine

definition.value: Deletion of UIS3 in Plasmodium yoelii provided attenuation and full protection in mice by Pyuis3(-) sporozoites required at least 2 immunizations against challenges with infectious sporozoites

label.value: Toxoplasma gondii mic2 mutant vaccine

definition.value: A mic2 mutant is attenuated in mice and induces protection from challenge with wild type T. gondii

label.value: Toxoplasma gondii OMPDC mutant vaccine

definition.value: An OMPDC mutant, alone or in combination with an UP mutation, is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type T. gondii

label.value: Toxoplasma gondii OMPDC/UP mutant vaccine

definition.value: A UP mutant, in combination with an OMPDC mutation, is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from wild type T. gondii
An OMPDC mutant, alone or in combination with an UP mutation, is attenuated in mice and induces significant protection from challenge with wild type T. gondii

label.value: intragastric route

definition.value: A route of administration that located in the stomach, so that the material is taken into body through stomach directly.
